Comment: susiesseniordogs said "This is incredible -- one day after her post, Cascade got adopted!!! 6 year old Cascade was posted on Monday. She had been living at her shelter in Arizona since the summer, she had no adoption prospects in sight and she was quite literally wasting away. Shelter life was very hard on Cascade.

Well, an extraordinary woman named Liddie and her family immediately stepped in to help this aging gal. A few hours after Cascade's post went online, Liddie loaded up the car with her dogs and drove on over to the shelter for a doggy meet and greet. At the time, we weren't sure how Cassie (as she is now called) was with children, but they quickly figured that out. Yesterday, Cassie went home with her new family. Forever!

This is a photo of Cassie (on the left) with her new sisters. 
And that, folks, is how you get an adoption done. Thank you, thank you, thank you to Cassie's new, amazing family! ‚ù§Ô∏è #seniordog #adopted"
